# Scoring Protocol

## When to Activate
- Any feedback, review, or QA evaluation task
- Spec completeness checks (PO/PM)
- Code review scoring (CTO, QA)
- Visual QA scoring (Designer, Frontend Dev)
- Test coverage assessment (Test Writer)

## Core Concepts

All agent feedback uses a single scoring format. This ensures consistency across agents and enables automated quality gates.

## Scoring Format

```
### Score: {total}/100

| Item | Score | Deduction Reason |
|------|-------|-----------------|
| {item1} | {score}/{weight} | {specific reason or "None"} |
| {item2} | {score}/{weight} | {specific reason or "None"} |
| ... | ... | ... |
```

## Severity Thresholds

| Range | Action |
|-------|--------|
| 90-100 | Ready to merge immediately |
| 80-89 | Minor fixes, then merge |
| 70-79 | Fixes needed, re-review required |
| 60-69 | Significant rework, 1 revision chance |
| Below 60 | Immediate failure, redesign required |

## Guidelines
1. Always provide specific deduction reasons — never deduct without explanation
2. Never give a perfect 100 without explicit justification
3. Weight scoring items by importance to the deliverable
4. Score objectively against acceptance criteria, not subjective preference

## Examples
- "Spec completeness 85/100 — Error handling scenarios missing (-10), edge cases undefined (-5)"
- "Visual quality 88/100 — Mobile spacing mismatch (-7), hover state not implemented (-5)"
- "QA overall 79/100 — E2E error scenarios uncovered (-8), mobile layout broken (-7), 3 uses of type any (-6)"

## Integration
- All agents reference this skill for evaluation tasks
- Thresholds drive the failure modes defined in CLAUDE.md
